    "created_at": "2015-09-19T19:34:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-19T19:34:33Z",
    "body": "If I set Gnome scaling to 1x (`gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface scaling-factor 1`), the native menus are properly sized but everything else is half sized. I wonder if this has to do with the way Linux Mint Cinnamon specifically handles interface scaling. Many other distros have half sized scrollbars and window decorations, even when setting Gnome scaling to 2x. Mint doesn't and I think that might be causing a problem with Electron.\n"
  },
